cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about improving the accuracy of object detection using a modified YOLOv2 approach. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a new loss function and uses deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to sub-categories such as machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on datasets, indicating that it could also belong to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
